main event: An observation of a UFO was documented in Roswell, New Mexico on 6 Oct 61.
interesting points: The object was described as a line well-executed sighting highly similar to earth survey picture., The observation lasted for 10 seconds., The weather was clear with excellent visibility at the time of observation., The observer had previous experience with meteorite activity and believed this did not fall within the natural astronomical bodies category., Local news had speculated about a new Russian satellite attempt around the time of the sighting.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object resembling a line
witness description: a Captain, command pilot, maintenance officer, reliability is excellent
